Professional sports teams seem to easily understand that men and women are not physically equal (in general) and wouldn't mess around with co-ed teams; yet we as a country will potentially risk soldiers lives by allowing gender politics to interfere with sound decisions about armed combat service.

column27: I agree with equal financial compensation for men & women at any work place, including the military. But given the prevailing military culture where women go through physical and psychological abuse by their male counterparts,  and also taking into consideration the fact that although both male and female prisoners of war are at risk of torture and rape by enemies, misogynistic societies may be more willing to abuse woman prisoners. Therefore I strongly disagree with equal obligation of citizenship such as signing up for the military draft.
